preview_comments.text: Do you also have storage problems?

@lazerlukki I don’t think so. I do overflow with my builds and I used to use a lot of buffer storage space ‘till I realize it’s completely unnecessary. I have a central storage space that has 2 industrial storage containers dedicated to every item I plan on automating though. For this build I just needed a way to end the walkways I have without them just running around the perimeter and then just ending the next foundation in which looks terrible. I wound up making a building to hide the seem for the walkways and needed to fill it with something to make it look nice so I used the storage containers. 😛

So i finished Bendy and the ink machine today. I have some thoughts about this game. It was totally a good game, the graphics are well done, the character designs are well polished and looked like the ink blot cartoon characters in 3D but the ending is kinda bland for me cuz the twist that the protagonist is stuck on a endless loop was kinda predictable. However, I enjoyed this game and the characters . I heard the sequel is coming soon in this fall and I wonder if it’s going to be way more scarier.🧐 Anyways, I hope y’all enjoy my drawing and I know it’s kinda early for Inktober because I’m participating Inktober in some parts. #inktober2019 #inktober #bendyandtheinkmachine #fanart #sketches #videogames #horror #joeydrewstudios #batim #batdr #bendyandthedarkrevival #bendyandtheinkmachinefanart #inksketches #inkblotcartoons

This year is the 30th anniversary of the release of the Sega Genesis in the United States. They released a Genesis mini console to commemorate the anniversary. As a hardcore Genesis fan, it was only right to pick one up. I have a Genesis 2 and 3 but I didn’t have a working OG version. This makes up for it in a miniaturized sleek way. Here are my 10 favorite Genesis games:
Honorable Mention: Comix Zone Vectorman, Sonic 2, Castlevania Bloodlines, Rocket Knight Adventures, Eternal Champions, Ecco the Dolphin, Columns and The Adventures Of Batman & Robin

8. Shinobi 3

6. NBA Live 95 
5. Shining Force 
4. Phantasy Star 4

1. Shining Force 2

caption.text:
Ni no Kuni: Wrath of the White Witch

It is a role-playing video game, developed by Level-5. It was released for the PlayStation 3 in Japan in November 2011, and published in Western regions by Namco Bandai Games in January 2013. It was also released for Nintendo Switch in September 2019, alongside a remastered version for Microsoft Windows and PlayStation 4. The game is a significantly enhanced version of Ni no Kuni: Dominion of the Dark Djinn, which originally released for the Nintendo DS in Japan in December 2010.

caption.text:
É extremamente comum em um jogo você ter vários aspectos que se repetem, inimigos, objetos no cenário, itens e etc. 
Por isso também é bastante comum nós podermos generalizar essas coisas e reutiliza-lás. …
Pegue o exemplo de um personagem principal, ele vai estar EM TODAS AS FASES! Kkkk
Agora imagine o fluxo -> Criar uma cena nova -> Colocar um SKSpriteNode -> Colocar a textura do personagem -> Seta as animações -> Os componentes -> Roda o jogo

Agora pense que seu jogo tem 30 fases distintas… Isso irá se repetir 30 vezes, kkkk. 
Pior… Na 27 fase você percebeu que a escala podia ser melhorada, aumentar só um pouquinho, você terá que voltar em cada fase e ajustar isso, certo?

Pois bem, chega de fazer as coisas no Go horsing… trago a vocês a tal solução…
SKReferenceNode
Esse lindo, é um node que simplesmente é uma referência a uma outra cena! Então numa cena podemos fazer o personagem principal e em todas as outras 30 só referenciaremos ela. Relaxa que não pesa já que é só uma referência!
E você também pode modificar a vontade dentro de uma cena específica se quiser algo especializado para tal cena, ou modificar na cena “mestre” e assim em todos os lugares que ela estiver sendo referenciada a modificação será aplicada! Show né?

MCoC October Update!
•
Three new champs are joining this month, Guillotine 2099, Elsa Bloodstone, and Man-Thing!
•
The first loading screen are all original characters made by Kabam, the company who makes this game. Guillotine 2099 is the futuristic version of Guillotine, a French hero out for souls.
•
Elsa is not pictured, but she is a vampire hunter and uses a rifle, a pistol, and super human abilities from her amulet.
•
Man-Thing lurks in swamps and can infect people with poison. He is pretty big, so watch out. He’s basically Swamp thing from dc but cooler lol

Reposted using @EasyRepost "Detienen al hijo de Jorge Oñate en el aeropuerto El Dorado .

La Policía Metropolitana de Bogotá confirmó que fue detenido Jorge Luis Oñate Zuleta, hijo del cantante vallenato Jorge Oñate, en el aeropuerto El Dorado.
Según las autoridades, a Oñate Zuleta le pidieron una requisa y él se negó, razón por la cual habría empezado una confrontación verbal del hijo con los operarios de El Dorado .

Minutos después, la discusión se calentó y resultó en golpes del artista contra un funcionario de esta terminal aérea .

Oñate Zuleta fue requerido por supervisor de Opain en la oficina de la Policía que queda en El Dorado, pero él no quiso y golpeó a otro funcionario .

La Policía afirmó que el altercado se habría presentado cuando el sujeto se dirigía a Valledupar, en el departamento del Cesar, en un vuelo de Avianca .

Varios agentes trasladaron a Oñate Zuleta a la Unidad de Reacción Inmediata (URI) de La Granja, de la localidad de Engativá .

Algunas personas afirman que el hijo del cantante vallenato habría amenazado de muerte a los funcionarios. Este hecho está siendo objeto de investigación por parte de las autoridades .

@LaFMOficial @blogvallenato" by @portalvallenato

Victory Viper Nightmare 
Sleek Model
A long time ago, I decided to build the ever-iconic Vic Viper from Gradius, that so many other builders had tackled before me. This particular model is loosely based off of the Salamander Viper, and sports a wicked color scheme :D
Surprisingly, it's armaments are rather light
2x Wingwraith Electric Energy Dash Cannons (projectiles are extremely fast)
1x Dual Hidden Energy Missile Launchers

There were many times when I came across the same crimson billboard on Crosby Lafeyette, seeing Arthur Morgan holding a revolver at me. And indeed I was blown away by the immersed world of Red Dead, foreverly trapped inside of a 19th century landscape. The painterly experience of being a Western outlaw, catching ghost trains and hunting gators by the bayou at night. Although they use to sit by the fire sharing stories together, but it is the portable solitude of gaslighting that allows the poetic of the night to walk while introspect
